Package com.alexgilleran.icesoap.request

Interface Summary
ListRequest<ResultType,SOAPFaultType> This request deals specifically with SOAP calls that recall a list of items, allowing listeners to be bound that will be called every time a new object is parsed rather than waiting until the entire request is finished.
Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType> Encapsulates all the code for making a SOAP Request - to use, create an object that implements the SOAP11Observer class (generally this is easiest using anonymous objects from the activity or fragment) and attach it using the Request#registerObserver(SOAP11Observer) method.
RequestFactory Creates Requests, passing them a default, Apache HTTP Client based SOAPRequester implementation.
SOAP11ListRequest<ResultType> Extension of ListRequest that specifies a standard SOAP11Fault rather than specifying a specific one.
SOAP11Request<ResultType> Encapsulates all the code for making a SOAP Request - to use, create an object that implements the SOAP11Observer class (generally this is easiest using anonymous objects from the activity or fragment) and attach it using the Request#registerObserver(SOAP11Observer) method.
SOAPRequester Handles SOAP requests Ideally this should allow for transport-independent resolution of SOAP requests but unfortunately the handling of HTTP errors inside the Request object makes this a fairly leaky abstraction - stay tuned for a fix.
